## High-level description
This YAML file defines a configuration for a feature flag system. It specifies a single flag with unsupported type, likely used for testing purposes to handle cases where an unsupported flag type is encountered.

## Symbols

### `version`
#### Description
Specifies the version of the configuration format being used.

#### Inputs
| Name | Type | Description |
|:-----|:-----|:------------|
| version | string | The version number of the configuration format |

### `flags`
#### Description
An array containing the definitions of feature flags.

#### Inputs
| Name | Type | Description |
|:-----|:-----|:------------|
| flags | array | A list of feature flag definitions |

### `flag1`
#### Description
Defines a single feature flag with an unsupported type.

#### Inputs
| Name | Type | Description |
|:-----|:-----|:------------|
| key | string | The unique identifier for the flag |
| name | string | The display name of the flag |
| type | string | The type of the flag (in this case, an unsupported type) |
| description | string | A brief description of the flag's purpose |
| enabled | boolean | Indicates whether the flag is enabled or not |

## Configuration
| Option | Type | Default | Description |
|:-------|:-----|:--------|:------------|
| key | string | "flag1" | The unique identifier for the flag |
| name | string | "flag1" | The display name of the flag |
| type | string | "VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE" | An unsupported flag type |
| description | string | "description" | A brief description of the flag |
| enabled | boolean | true | Indicates that the flag is enabled |

## Error Handling
This file is likely used for testing error handling in a feature flag system. The unsupported "VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE" is probably intended to trigger error handling or validation mechanisms in the system that processes this configuration.
